channel.title: 718 Run error
channel.description:
so i was editing shop locations, and added server to eclipse and when i randomly started getting this run error, both compile and run are using the same JDK, not sure what i did. :palm:
[code][GTLVote V1.1] Settings initializing... Exception in thread "main" java.lang.UnsupportedClassVersionError: com/mysql/jdb c/Driver : Unsupported major.minor version 52.0 at java.lang.ClassLoader.defineClass1(Native Method) at java.lang.ClassLoader.defineClass(ClassLoader.java:800) at java.security.SecureClassLoader.defineClass(SecureClassLoader.java:14 2) at java.net.URLClassLoader.defineClass(URLClassLoader.java:449) at java.net.URLClassLoader.access$100(URLClassLoader.java:71) at java.net.URLClassLoader$1.run(URLClassLoader.java:361) at java.net.URLClassLoader$1.run(URLClassLoader.java:355) at java.security.AccessController.doPrivileged(Native Method) at java.net.URLClassLoader.findClass(URLClassLoader.java:354) at java.lang.ClassLoader.loadClass(ClassLoader.java:425) at sun.misc.Launcher$AppClassLoader.loadClass(Launcher.java:308) at java.lang.ClassLoader.loadClass(ClassLoader.java:358) at java.lang.Class.forName0(Native Method) at java.lang.Class.forName(Class.java:191) at org.Vote.Connect.connect(Connect.java:17) at org.Vote.MainLoader.<init>(MainLoader.java:22) at com.rs.Launcher.<clinit>(Launcher.java:137) Press any key to continue . . .[/code]

item.title: 718 Run error
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Well… The error specified is because a file or files were compiled on Java 1.8. And you’re running it on Java version 1.7

Again. Upgrade to 1.8, and change all your compilers/run.bats/Environmental Variables.
And then recompile, then run.

item.title: 718 Run error
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

You compiled a file on JDK 1.8, and are trying to run the file using a lower version of Java.

Remove any version of Java that is lower than version 1.8, and make sure to edit your run.bat/compiler accordingly.

If you manually did your environmental variables (windows usually), then you need to update those as well.
